Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.93,0:04:52.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,大家好\N{\fs90}Hello, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.42,0:04:58.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,掌声送给温室花朵乐队\N{\fs90}Hello. That was the Hothouse Flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:05:00.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在我们看到这位\N{\fs90}And now, look what we have here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.50,0:05:05.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,他生于-\N{\fs90}He was born-
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.82,0:05:10.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,他生于1836年...\N{\fs90}He was born in 1836...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.38,0:05:13.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,他曾让 汽车杂志 给炒鱿鱼了\N{\fs90}He was fired by Car magazine
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.12,0:05:15.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,让 机动车 杂志炒了\N{\fs90}fired by Autocar magazine
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.92,0:05:18.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,让 苏格兰周日报 炒了\N{\fs90}fired by Scotland On Sunday
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.10,0:05:19.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且\N{\fs90}and somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.30,0:05:24.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,他还能让沃尔沃经销商给炒了\N{\fs90}he managed to get fired by a Volvo dealership.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.06,0:05:25.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\fs90}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.41,0:05:27.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,可能就是因为开车太慢\N{\fs90}Probably for driving too slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.64,0:05:30.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,各位 詹姆士 梅\N{\fs90}Ladies and gentlemen, James May!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.49,0:05:40.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢大家 你们太热情了\N{\fs90}Thank you, thank you. You're very kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.37,0:05:42.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 女士们先生们\N{\fs90}And, ladies and gentlemen
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.98,0:05:46.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,接下来这位 后排的观众可能看不见他\N{\fs90}you probably can't see him from the back
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.54,0:05:51.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我保证 他在台上\N{\fs90}but I assure you he is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.58,0:05:54.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,他曾被约克电台给炒了\N{\fs90}He was fired by Radio York
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.34,0:05:56.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,被利兹电台炒了\N{\fs90}fired by Radio Leeds
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.81,0:05:58.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,被兰开夏电台炒了\N{\fs90}and fired by Radio Lancashire
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.97,0:06:00.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,这位就是 理查德 哈蒙德!\N{\fs90}it's Richard Hammond!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.64,0:06:05.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,大家好 谢谢你们的热情\N{\fs90}Hello! Hello! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.02,0:06:07.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\fs90}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.05,0:06:12.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们\N{\fs90}And, ladies and gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.86,0:06:16.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,这位\N{\fs90}Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.52,0:06:19.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,他 他基本上\N{\fs90}He's- He's basically
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.27,0:06:23.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,是一只剃了毛的猿 穿着人类的衬衫\N{\fs90}a shaved ape in a shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.22,0:06:26.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,严格意义上 他也是我们中唯一一个\N{\fs90}And he, technically, is the only one of us
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.89,0:06:29.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,从未被任何公司炒过鱿鱼的人\N{\fs90}never to be fired by anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:33.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,掌声欢迎杰里米 克拉克森\N{\fs90}It's Jeremy Clarkson!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.17,0:06:37.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢大家\N{\fs90}Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.65,0:06:39.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,好消息是\N{\fs90}And the good thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.81,0:06:43.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,我现在不太可能被炒鱿鱼了\N{\fs90}it's very unlikely I'm going to be fired now
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.13,0:06:46.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我们这是网络节目\N{\fs90}because we're on the Internet
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.21,0:06:48.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,这意味着 节目里我能和马快活快活了\N{\fs90}which means I could pleasure a horse
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.00,0:06:50.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,不行不行不行\N{\fs90}No! No No
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.48,0:06:51.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,-狗呢 -不\N{\fs90}-Dog? -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.70,0:06:53.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,严禁各种快活\N{\fs90}No pleasuring of any sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.77,0:06:56.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是全家一起看的节目  -好吧\N{\fs90}- There are families watching. - Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.30,0:06:59.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,说回正题 我们都是汽车记者\N{\fs90}Anyway, we are all car journalists.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.77,0:07:03.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,在过去20年间...\N{\fs90}And we have spent the last 20 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.29,0:07:05.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们一直在被炒鱿鱼  -可不是吗\N{\fs90}- Being fired. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.84,0:07:08.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我们已经将毕生所学\N{\fs90}But we have poured everything we know
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:14.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,和所关心的一切投入这个节目\N{\fs90}everything we care about, into this show
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.48,0:07:19.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,倾尽所有 接下来的短片\N{\fs90}Everything. And coming up now is a small montage
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.10,0:07:22.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,包含了未来12周你们要期待的所有精彩\N{\fs90}of what you can expect over the next 12 weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.06,0:07:34.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,准备好了吗 两位\N{\fs90}Are we ready, gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.00,0:07:35.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,讲真 我也不知道\N{\fs90}Honestly, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.98,0:07:45.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,夭寿\N{\fs90}Argh!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.14,0:07:48.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是坡太抖还是他的命根子出事了\N{\fs90}Is that the size of the drop or what's happened to his penis?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.78,0:07:53.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,你现在看到的东西叫壮观\N{\fs90}You're looking at magnificence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:55.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,救命 大事不好\N{\fs90}Help! This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.69,0:08:00.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆士说我们得停下来加油\N{\fs90}James says we've got to stop for fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.14,0:08:08.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,我恨你!\N{\fs90}I hate you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.85,0:08:10.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,他不喜欢我们呢\N{\fs90}He doesn't like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.26,0:08:16.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的天\N{\fs90}Bloody Nora!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.65,0:08:26.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,好像有点轻微漏水\N{\fs90}May be leaking slightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.34,0:08:27.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,傻犊子\N{\fs90}What a moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.02,0:08:32.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,你玩坏了我的豪华轿车\N{\fs90}You sunk my limousine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.73,0:08:34.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我鼻子里的卫生棉掉了一个\N{\fs90}I've lost one of my nose tampons.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.56,0:08:40.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不是一件很文明的事\N{\fs90}This is not a particularly cultural thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.70,0:08:44.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不喜欢晚上烧胎的味道\N{\fs90}I don't like the smell of tire smoke in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.96,0:08:46.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,赶紧回来\N{\fs90}Oi! Get back in!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.92,0:08:48.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆士要掉下去了...\N{\fs90}James is falling...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.06,0:08:58.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,穿亚麻西装漂移\N{\fs90}Sideways in linen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.33,0:09:13.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,这事很伤自尊 对吧 \N{\fs90}There's no dignity in that, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.22,0:09:14.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,对\N{\fs90}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.49,0:09:20.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢 非常感谢\N{\fs90}Thank you. Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.76,0:09:22.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,听我说 谢谢\N{\fs90}Now- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.56,0:09:26.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们将在这里给大家呈现以上所有内容\N{\fs90}All of that is gonna be hosted from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.61,0:09:30.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我们新的移动演播帐篷\N{\fs90}This is our new travelling studio tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.60,0:09:34.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常感谢 我们将在这里面环游世界\N{\fs90}Thank you so much. We're gonna be roaming the world in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.04,0:09:35.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像吉普赛人一样\N{\fs90}We're gonna be like gypsies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.47,0:09:38.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,不同的是我们开的车都会上保险\N{\fs90}Only the cars we drive are gonna be insured.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.24,0:09:40.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,不要再说这种害我们被炒掉的话了\N{\fs90}Stop saying things that are gonna get us fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.98,0:09:42.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,我只想说这太棒了\N{\fs90}But I'm just saying, it's brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.01,0:09:45.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的\N{\fs90}It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.85,0:09:49.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,喂 谁把我们的无人机打下来了\N{\fs90}Oi! Who shot our drone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.98,0:09:52.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,-有人开枪了吗 -是他\N{\fs90}- Did someone shoot it? - Him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.95,0:09:55.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,先不纠结这些了 好吗\N{\fs90}Let's not get bogged down in who shot what, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.93,0:09:58.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,咱们把衣服换了然后继续主持节目吧\N{\fs90}Let's get changed and get on with the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.03,0:10:01.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们该继续吗\N{\fs90}Shall we get on with the show?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.20,0:10:03.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 来吧\N{\fs90}Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.75,0:10:25.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢大家\N{\fs90}Thank you, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.61,0:10:27.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常感谢\N{\fs90}Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:31.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到史上第一期GT的现场\N{\fs90}And welcome to the first ever Grand Tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.10,0:10:41.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢 希望你们喜欢这个帐篷\N{\fs90}Thank you. Now, we hope you like our tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.07,0:10:44.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们觉得最棒的是 因为我们会带着它周游世界\N{\fs90}We think the great thing is that because it roams around the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.67,0:10:48.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以每周窗外的景色都不一样\N{\fs90}we get a different view out of the big picture windows every week.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.25,0:10:49.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,比如这周 很明显外面\N{\fs90}So this week, obviously we've got
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.96,0:10:52.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,是加州的莫哈维沙漠\N{\fs90}the high desert of California.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.39,0:10:54.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,-下周是哪里 没人知道  -我知道\N{\fs90}- Next week, who knows? - I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.75,0:10:58.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,废话 詹姆斯 我们当然知道 是约翰内斯堡\N{\fs90}Well, yes, James, we know. It's Johannesburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.82,0:11:02.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,-现在他们都知道了  -我知道 但是无所谓\N{\fs90}- Now they know. - I know they know! It doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.22,0:11:05.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,重要的是景色每周都变 观众也如此\N{\fs90}The point is the view changes and so does the audience, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.30,0:11:07.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,这周你们都是美国人\N{\fs90}This week you're all Americans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.24,0:11:17.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在有这么一个小问题\N{\fs90}Now, this is a bit of a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:20.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,对于我们这些说英语的人\N{\fs90}for people like us who speak English.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.61,0:11:24.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,在商店餐厅这些地方交流都没问题\N{\fs90}We can converse perfectly well in a shop or a restaurant,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.88,0:11:27.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,但当说到汽车与驾驶的时候\N{\fs90}but when it comes to cars and motoring,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.65,0:11:30.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们和我们用的词都不一样\N{\fs90}every single word you use is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.69,0:11:33.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的意思是你们说的都是错的\N{\fs90}When I say "different", I mean "wrong."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.66,0:11:36.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,那根用来换挡的杆子你们叫什么\N{\fs90}When you change gear with a lever, what do you call that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:38.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,- Stick  - Stick\N{\fs90}- Stick. - Stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.63,0:11:40.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,看好了 这才是Stick\N{\fs90}Now, you see, this is a stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.80,0:11:42.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,没法用这个换挡\N{\fs90}Couldn't change gear with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.90,0:11:45.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过倒是可以用来指指东西\N{\fs90}Wouldn't work. What you can do with this is point at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.64,0:11:47.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,我来给你们上一课\N{\fs90}Let's see if we can get you educated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.65,0:11:49.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,车的这部分你们叫什么\N{\fs90}What do you call this bit of a car?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.64,0:11:52.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,- The Hood  - Bonnet\N{\fs90}- The hood! - Bonnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.64,0:11:52.61,注释,,0,0,0,,hood又是帽衫的意思
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.64,0:11:55.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,- Bonnet - 他们在学习\N{\fs90}- Bonnet. - They're learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.18,0:11:58.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,你说什么 我当然知道不能把Bonnet戴头上\N{\fs90}What do you mean? I know you can wear a bonnet on your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.28,0:12:02.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,两种意思 我们是能够理解事物有两种意思的\N{\fs90}It's two things. We're capable of having those different thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:05.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这种车你们叫什么  -Pick-up\N{\fs90}- What type of vehicle is this? Pick -up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.42,0:12:06.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是的 这种车叫蠢\N{\fs90}No, it's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.99,0:12:10.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,-等等  -真的很蠢\N{\fs90}- Oh, now, hang on. - It is stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:12.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,再来个类似的\N{\fs90}Let's do another one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.63,0:12:16.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是什么车型  -Coupe\N{\fs90}- What type of vehicle is this? Coupe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.53,0:12:19.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,Coupe吗 Coop是用来养鸡的\N{\fs90}Coupe? Coop is where you keep your chickens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.53,0:12:19.68,注释,,0,0,0,,coop与coupe美语相近 coop 农业合作社
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.72,0:12:22.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,这叫Coupé 我承认这是个法语词\N{\fs90}That's a coupé. That's a French word, I admit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.40,0:12:24.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,- 是的  - 但他们把这个都搞混了\N{\fs90}- Yeah, a bit. - They're muddled with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.01,0:12:27.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们知道乔治布什曾经说过什么吗 有关法国人\N{\fs90}George Bush, have you heard what he once said about the French?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.81,0:12:29.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,他说 法国人的问题就在于 他们没有\N{\fs90}"The trouble with the French is they have no word
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.61,0:12:31.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,能够用来形容entrepreneur的词\N{\fs90}for entrepreneur."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.61,0:12:31.61,注释,,0,0,0,,entrepreneur：法语词，企业家
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.75,0:12:34.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,确实很难 我认为只有一个词是我们都认同的\N{\fs90}It is difficult. I think the only thing we agree on
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.95,0:12:37.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,- 方向盘 - 是的\N{\fs90}- is "steering wheel." - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.15,0:12:41.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,但他们又把方向盘的位置放反了\N{\fs90}But then they go and put it on the wrong side of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.36,0:12:45.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,一直这样开车一定挺麻烦的\N{\fs90}It must be really annoying having to drive along like that all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.83,0:12:48.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,就不能像我们一样 把方向盘放到驾驶员面前吗\N{\fs90}Why don't you just put it in front of the driver like we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.92,0:12:51.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得我们还是继续节目吧\N{\fs90}It's probably a good idea if we get on with the actual show.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.97,0:12:54.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,好主意 但要先澄清一下\N{\fs90}Yes, it is. But we had to clear all that up,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.34,0:12:56.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,和某些人的说法不同\N{\fs90}because contrary to what some people have been saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.71,0:12:59.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,这确实是一档汽车节目\N{\fs90}this actually is a car show.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.07,0:13:01.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-但下周不是  -下周是个特例\N{\fs90}- Well, not next week it isn't. - Next week is an exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.84,0:13:03.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的  -我们去巴巴多斯那期也不是\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - But not when we go to Barbados either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.78,0:13:06.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 巴巴多斯绝对也是一个特例\N{\fs90}No, Barbados is definitely another exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.67,0:13:09.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,但今晚绝对是一档纯正的汽车节目\N{\fs90}But tonight couldn't be more "car-y" if it tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.48,0:13:12.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,我会证明的 因为今天要以它开场\N{\fs90}I'm gonna prove that point because we're kicking off with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.69,0:13:19.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,等一下 等我说完\N{\fs90}Bear with me, bear with me-
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.66,0:13:22.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,我同意\N{\fs90}I agree!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.43,0:13:23.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想说的是\N{\fs90}The thing is, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.60,0:13:25.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在许多超级跑车制造商采用了\N{\fs90}various supercar makers have now taken
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.00,0:13:29.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,和普锐斯相同的保护生态环境技术\N{\fs90}the polar-bear-friendly technology from a Prius,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.84,0:13:33.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,只不过是用来创造原始 野蛮的速度\N{\fs90}and they are now using it to create raw, naked speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.68,0:13:36.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得在所有这些混动究极跑车中 最棒的是\N{\fs90}Now, I say the best of these hybrid hypercars
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.95,0:13:40.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,那辆疯狂的 斜着眼睛的迈凯伦P1\N{\fs90}is the mad, swivel-eyed McLaren P1.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.20,0:13:43.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,而理查德 哈蒙德错误地认为\N{\fs90}Whereas Richard Hammond, who's wrong-
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.42,0:13:44.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,我没错\N{\fs90}I'm not wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.49,0:13:46.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,他错误地认为最棒的是\N{\fs90}He is, because he says the best
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.75,0:13:49.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,那辆无聊的保时捷918\N{\fs90}is actually the rather boring Porsche 918.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.99,0:13:52.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,-一点也不无聊  -无聊\N{\fs90}- It's not boring! - Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.53,0:13:54.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不无聊  -真的\N{\fs90}- It isn't. - Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.31,0:13:56.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 随你怎么说\N{\fs90}It isn't. Well, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.03,0:13:59.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们决定开着这两辆车碰个头\N{\fs90}We decided to meet up with the cars
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.08,0:14:02.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后终结这场争论\N{\fs90}and settle this once and for all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.83,0:15:04.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,这场史诗对决的地点选在了葡萄牙\N{\fs90}The location we chose for this titanic duel was Portugal...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.78,0:15:09.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,再具体点就是在阿尔加维赛道\N{\fs90}specifically, the international race track of the Algarve.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.01,0:15:18.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们刚到 保时捷和迈凯伦的技术人员\N{\fs90}When we arrived, mechanics from Porsche
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.85,0:15:21.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,就立刻扑向了我们的车\N{\fs90}and McLaren pounced on our cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.47,0:15:23.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,为接下来的对决做准备\N{\fs90}fettling them for what was to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.02,0:15:27.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,这也意味着哈蒙德和我有时间\N{\fs90}And this meant Hammond and I had some time to indulge
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.12,0:15:31.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,来做一些幼稚的评头论足\N{\fs90}in a spot of childish point scoring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.09,0:15:34.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,哪辆车在这个赛道上是最快的\N{\fs90}Which one of these is going to be the fastest around this track?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.36,0:15:35.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这辆吗  -是的\N{\fs90}- This? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.73,0:15:38.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,除了这辆 哪辆更快\N{\fs90}Apart from this one, which will be faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.03,0:15:40.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,不可能 你认为哪辆车最快\N{\fs90}It won't. Which one do you think will be the fastest?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.70,0:15:42.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这辆  -这辆\N{\fs90}- This one. - This one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.60,0:15:45.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以两边都觉得自己的车最快\N{\fs90}Porsche think the Porsche will be fastest. McLaren say the McLaren.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.94,0:15:48.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我要买的话这车多少钱\N{\fs90}How much is it if I wanted to buy one?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.04,0:15:51.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我记得有一辆被拍卖到了180万\N{\fs90}I think one was sold in an auction for 1.8 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.61,0:15:55.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,180万美元 哈蒙德 你的多少钱\N{\fs90}1.8 million dollars. Hammond, how much is yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.15,0:15:57.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,838欧元\N{\fs90}838 euros.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.12,0:15:59.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,-单位是千吗  -是的\N{\fs90}- Thousand I'm guessing? - Yes. It is thousands.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.02,0:16:02.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么你的车门上有个数字\N{\fs90}Why has your car got a number on the side?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.89,0:16:04.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是Weissach特别版\N{\fs90}It's the Weissach edition, this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.89,0:16:06.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,-它还配有钛合金底盘螺栓 -太蠢了\N{\fs90}- You also get titanium chassis bolts. - Stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.96,0:16:09.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,只需要多花上6万英镑\N{\fs90}For just an extra ?60.000.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.06,0:16:12.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有个碳纤维引擎盖支架\N{\fs90}And a carbon-fiber bonnet strut.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.90,0:16:14.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看 能省出多少重量来着\N{\fs90}Look at that. How much does that save?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.30,0:16:17.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,-大概100克  -不错吧 100克呢\N{\fs90}- About 100 grams. - Right there, 100 grams.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.32,0:16:20.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,迈凯伦有没有碳纤维引擎盖支架\N{\fs90}Has the McLaren got a carbon-fiber bonnet strut?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.27,0:16:23.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们不需要 -我不需要支起引擎盖\N{\fs90}- Doesn't need one. - No, because my bonnet doesn't go up
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.68,0:16:26.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它永远不会抛锚\N{\fs90}because it will never break down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.05,0:16:28.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且它还有两扇呆门 正常门 呆门\N{\fs90}And it's got silly doors. Proper doors, silly doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.02,0:16:32.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的百公里油耗只有8.3升\N{\fs90}Mine does 34 miles to the gallon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.66,0:16:34.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,我只有3升\N{\fs90}This does 94.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.89,0:16:37.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,-百公里才3升吗  -3升\N{\fs90}- 94 miles to the gallon? - 94mpg.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.09,0:16:39.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,提醒我一下 保时捷的母公司是\N{\fs90}Just remind me, Porsche is owned by?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.26,0:16:41.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,大众\N{\fs90}That'll be Volkswagen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.60,0:16:51.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快这两辆车都已准备好下赛道了\N{\fs90}Soon the McLaren and the Porsche were ready for some shakedown laps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.08,0:16:58.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们决定先开一开对方的车\N{\fs90}And for these we decided we'd drive each other's cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.98,0:17:04.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,一上来我就能告诉你\N{\fs90}Straight away, I can tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.79,0:17:08.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆车没有迈凯伦的\N{\fs90}that this doesn't have the brutality or the savagery
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.29,0:17:11.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,那种残暴和野蛮\N{\fs90}of the McLaren.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.19,0:17:15.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它有后轮转向和四轮驱动\N{\fs90}Because it has rear-wheel steering and four-wheel drive,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.26,0:17:18.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,让人感觉很放心和安全\N{\fs90}it feels secure and safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.13,0:17:20.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,而这也会给你信心\N{\fs90}And that gives you the confidence-
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.80,0:17:24.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,让你自由发挥\N{\fs90}...to play about.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.42,0:17:39.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我用迈凯伦以这个速度过这个弯\N{\fs90}If I went round this corner this fast in the McLaren...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.42,0:17:43.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,会有很多翔跑出来的\N{\fs90}...a lot of poo would come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.86,0:17:52.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,已经有翔跑出来了\N{\fs90}Whoa! There's poo coming out now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.00,0:17:58.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,天啊\N{\fs90}Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.04,0:18:01.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,轮胎在六档还特么的打滑\N{\fs90}It's spinning its wheels in sixth!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.95,0:18:09.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车太吓人了\N{\fs90}This is frightening, that's what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.82,0:18:14.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,哇 更多的翔\N{\fs90}Whoa! More poo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.66,0:18:18.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我从没想到一个人会因吓出的翔太多而死\N{\fs90}I didn't think it was possible to shit yourself to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.21,0:18:35.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,抓地力实在是太棒了\N{\fs90}The grip is genuinely incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.91,0:18:42.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,这才对嘛\N{\fs90}Oh, there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.52,0:18:45.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这辆残暴而无情的P1里\N{\fs90}In the savage and unforgiving P1,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:48.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,我脆弱的神经都碎成了渣渣\N{\fs90}my nerves were shot to pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.23,0:18:51.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,但也深深地爱上了它\N{\fs90}But I, too, was falling in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.29,0:18:53.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,903匹马力\N{\fs90}903 horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.46,0:18:58.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,上帝啊\N{\fs90}Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.57,0:19:02.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,你这个淘气的坏家伙\N{\fs90}Oh, you bad, bad, naughty car!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:09.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,天呐\N{\fs90}Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.05,0:19:13.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆车会刷新你的认知\N{\fs90}This recalibrates your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.35,0:19:16.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我本以为没有车能像918那样充满激情\N{\fs90}I didn't think anything could be as exciting as that Porsche,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.62,0:19:19.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是它做到了\N{\fs90}but this- this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.89,0:19:24.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆车太棒了\N{\fs90}This is brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.46,0:19:30.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的太棒了\N{\fs90}Absolutely brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.53,0:19:32.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢\N{\fs90}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.53,0:19:34.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,一辆神奇的车\N{\fs90}What a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.34,0:19:36.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,我太爱它了\N{\fs90}I love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.74,0:19:41.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,-怎么样  -真是辆破车\N{\fs90}- Well? - This is rubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.58,0:19:43.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,巧了 我也是这么想的\N{\fs90}I was just thinking exactly the same about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.98,0:19:45.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是吗  -它无聊到让我想死\N{\fs90}- Were you? - This was boring me to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.65,0:19:50.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,像维多利亚时期的女性小说一样无聊\N{\fs90}It was like being stuck in a Victorian woman's novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.15,0:19:54.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,总比和一只发疯的猩猩被困在一个电话亭里强\N{\fs90}I'd rather that than being stuck in a telephone box with a panicking gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:19:55.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,- 破车  - 它想杀了我\N{\fs90}- Rubbish.- It was trying to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.47,0:19:58.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,- 它一直想害死我  - 我就喜欢这点\N{\fs90}- It wants to hurt me.- That's why I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.39,0:20:00.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆车就好比传教士体位\N{\fs90}This is a missionary-position car.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.59,0:20:03.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,外科医生手中的刀片\N{\fs90}Razor blade in the hands of a surgeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.33,0:20:05.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,醉酒农民手中的镰刀\N{\fs90}Sickle in the hands of a drunk peasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.99,0:20:09.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,唐顿庄园 绝命毒师 那是冰毒\N{\fs90}Downton Abbey. Breaking Bad. That's crystal meth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.70,0:20:11.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一捆大麻\N{\fs90}That's some iffy weed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.33,0:20:14.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,一瓶上等红酒 一箱纽卡索啤酒\N{\fs90}Fine wine. Crate of Newcy Brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.04,0:20:19.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,大杯雪莉酒 苦艾酒\N{\fs90}Schooner of sherry. Absinthe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.11,0:20:20.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯邦德吩咐\N{\fs90}James Bond specifying
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.84,0:20:22.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,马天尼是用摇的而不能搅\N{\fs90}his martini to be shaken not stirred.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.91,0:20:24.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,猜火车里的贝格比\N{\fs90}Begbie in Trainspotting
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.41,0:20:26.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,在夜店把啤酒杯抛过自己的肩膀\N{\fs90}lobbing a pint pot over his shoulder in a night club
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.25,0:20:29.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后干一架 咋了\N{\fs90}and starting a bar fight. What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.92,0:20:35.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们好呀\N{\fs90}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.59,0:20:37.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,你来干什么\N{\fs90}What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.56,0:20:39.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,二位 我来是因为\N{\fs90}I'm here because, gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:41.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我卡车的后面有一辆\N{\fs90}I have in the back of that lorry
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.50,0:20:44.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,使你们的迈凯伦和保时捷\N{\fs90}something that will make your McLaren and your Porsche
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.37,0:20:46.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,看起来相形见绌的车\N{\fs90}look like lumps of yesteryear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.73,0:21:16.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想不起来上次一辆车\N{\fs90}I cannot remember the last time a car,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.67,0:21:18.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者其他任何东西\N{\fs90}or, indeed, any sort of thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.53,0:21:21.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,像拉法一样让我如此兴奋了\N{\fs90}gave me a fizz like the Ferrari LaFerrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.10,0:21:26.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆车有950匹马力\N{\fs90}This has 950 horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.18,0:21:28.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,950匹啊\N{\fs90}950.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.11,0:21:30.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,马力比其他两辆都大\N{\fs90}More than either of the other two.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.94,0:21:33.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且还更轻 只有1250公斤\N{\fs90}And it's lighter. It weighs 1.250 kilograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.68,0:21:39.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,这比大部分掀背车都轻\N{\fs90}Which is less than most hatchbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.36,0:21:44.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,实际上拉法的本事还不止于此\N{\fs90}Actually there is a bit more to the Ferrari LaFerrari,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.63,0:21:49.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它配备了F1的KERS系统\N{\fs90}because what it has is, in effect, a formula one KERS system.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.50,0:21:54.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,能够随时通过电机和电池\N{\fs90}It constantly recovers energy that would otherwise be lost
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.34,0:21:56.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,回收原本会被浪费的能量\N{\fs90}using its electric motor and its battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.74,0:21:59.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以当我踩下刹车的时候\N{\fs90}So as I brake there,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.51,0:22:03.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,车子其实在说 这些能量我全要了\N{\fs90}the car is actually saying, "That energy, I'll have that."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.31,0:22:05.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,大直道\N{\fs90}Straight!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.78,0:22:11.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,这才是950匹马力应有的感觉\N{\fs90}This is what 950 horsepower feels like!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.06,0:22:17.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,天呐\N{\fs90}Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.03,0:22:26.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,我相信它能够碾碎那两辆车\N{\fs90}This I believe will absolutely mince the other two.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.47,0:22:28.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,这速度\N{\fs90}Oh, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.07,0:22:32.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯显然在鬼扯\N{\fs90}James was obviously talking nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.84,0:22:35.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,但毫无疑问的是\N{\fs90}But there's no getting around the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.54,0:22:37.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,这三台车将汽车科技\N{\fs90}that these three cars take automotive science
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.81,0:22:39.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,带入了新纪元\N{\fs90}to a new level.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.02,0:22:44.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们运用最新的环保技术\N{\fs90}They use the latest green technology
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.79,0:22:47.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,从每滴燃油中\N{\fs90}to squeeze as much speed as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.52,0:22:50.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,压榨出更多速度\N{\fs90}from every molecule of fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.83,0:22:55.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,结果便是 它们都有能力\N{\fs90}As a result, they're all capable of blasting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.03,0:22:57.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,在极速超过 320Km/h 的同时\N{\fs90}way past 200 miles an hour
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:23:01.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,排出比家用车还少的有害物质\N{\fs90}whilst producing fewer harmful emissions than a family saloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.11,0:23:11.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是三台令人难以置信的机器\N{\fs90}What we have here, then, are three incredible machines
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.85,0:23:13.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们的横空出世\N{\fs90}which, at a stroke,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.65,0:23:16.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,使传统的超级跑车显得\N{\fs90}have made the traditional supercar look wooden...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.92,0:23:18.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,既简陋又落后\N{\fs90}and old-fashioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.62,0:23:25.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,各位 欢迎来到三神车的世界\N{\fs90}Welcome, everyone, to the hypercar holy trinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.80,0:23:33.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,左后视镜里是价值100万英镑的保时捷\N{\fs90}In that door mirror I have a one million Porsche.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.25,0:23:37.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,右后视镜里是价值100万英镑的法拉利\N{\fs90}In that door mirror I have a one million Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.97,0:23:41.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,今天真是玩过瘾了\N{\fs90}What a toy box today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.42,0:23:50.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,大猩猩的屁股冒出了火花\N{\fs90}Sparks from Jezzer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.02,0:23:59.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,你干不掉我的 哈蒙德\N{\fs90}I don't think so, Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.50,0:24:08.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,这应该相当昂贵\N{\fs90}This could be so expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.48,0:24:20.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要提速了\N{\fs90}It's going to boost.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.72,0:24:22.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,按下 IPAS\N{\fs90}Pushing the IPAS button!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.88,0:24:26.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,我额外获得了170匹马力\N{\fs90}And that gives me another 170 horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.69,0:24:31.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,启动 DRS\N{\fs90}Opening DRS!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.29,0:24:35.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢我的天啊\N{\fs90}Oh, my Christ!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.33,0:24:37.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,太快了\N{\fs90}Bloody...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.66,0:24:40.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,开着拉法的梅来了\N{\fs90}And here comes May in the Ferrari LaFerrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.74,0:24:48.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,集中精神 不要分心\N{\fs90}Concentrating. Concentrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.59,0:25:02.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢吼 那辆该死的车\N{\fs90}Oh-oh! That bloody car
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.99,0:25:04.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不在里面的时候也想搞死我\N{\fs90}is trying to kill me, and I'm not even in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.56,0:25:08.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈哈\N{\fs90}Ha-ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.34,0:25:23.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们本可这样玩一整天\N{\fs90}We could have played out there all day,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.21,0:25:26.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,但在一场价值300万英镑的车祸发生之前\N{\fs90}but before we ended up in a three million pound crash,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.88,0:25:28.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们决定还是先开始测试\N{\fs90}we decided to start the tests
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.88,0:25:31.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看谁的车才是最好的\N{\fs90}to see which of the cars was best.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.75,0:25:33.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想出了第一个测试\N{\fs90}I came up with the first one,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.39,0:25:36.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,主要是为了欺负梅这个不速之客\N{\fs90}mainly to annoy gate-crasher May.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.66,0:25:39.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,咱们的第一个测试是直线加速赛\N{\fs90}Let's make the first test a drag race
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.86,0:25:43.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,-但只能用电能 -好主意\N{\fs90}- using electrical power only. - Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.83,0:25:46.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,-才不是呢  -为什么\N{\fs90}- It isn't a good idea. - Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.53,0:25:49.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为拉法不能用纯电驱动\N{\fs90}Because you can't drive the Ferrari on electrical power only.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.41,0:25:52.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不是吧  -当然不能了\N{\fs90}- No! - Of course you can't,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.37,0:25:54.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它用的是类似F1的KERS系统\N{\fs90}because it's a KERS system like a Formula One car.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.48,0:25:57.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,有一台V12引擎和一个电动机\N{\fs90}It's got a V12 engine and an electric motor,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.38,0:26:00.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,但二者是集成的 只能同时工作\N{\fs90}but they are integrated, they work together, you can't separate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.67,0:26:03.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你早就该想到的 不是吗  -大意了吧\N{\fs90}- You should have thought about that, shouldn't you? - Bad planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.59,0:26:08.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,把詹姆斯贬为旁观者之后\N{\fs90}With James reduced to the role of onlooker,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.39,0:26:12.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我俩把P1和918摆到了起点\N{\fs90}we lined up the P1 and the 918 on the start line,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.24,0:26:16.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我们并没有轰油门\N{\fs90}but then, instead of revving the petrol engines,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.06,0:26:18.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,而是关掉发动机\N{\fs90}we shut them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.60,0:26:24.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,太诡异了\N{\fs90}That is weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.64,0:26:27.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,在一片寂静中准备\N{\fs90}Preparing to start a drag race
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.98,0:26:30.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,开始一场直线加速赛\N{\fs90}in complete silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.31,0:26:32.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,我现在仍然拥有两个电动机\N{\fs90}I still have two electric motors
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.95,0:26:36.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,总共能产生285匹的马力\N{\fs90}that together produce 285 brake horsepower
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.32,0:26:37.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,比他那辆迈凯伦\N{\fs90}which is 109 more
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.92,0:26:43.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,上面的单电机要多了109匹 噢耶\N{\fs90}than the one electric motor in his McLaren. Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.43,0:26:55.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,我先走一步\N{\fs90}I'm outta here!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.60,0:26:58.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,你一定会喜欢电动机\N{\fs90}You've got to love that, the immediate power
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.27,0:27:00.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,这种直接的动力输出\N{\fs90}from an electrical engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.67,0:27:04.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在时速已经超过110公里了 但还是不够快\N{\fs90}That is 70 miles an hour already and it isn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.46,0:27:20.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,刚才谁赢了 是我吗\N{\fs90}Who won that? It was me, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.53,0:27:22.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,是你赢了 但这并不重要\N{\fs90}Yeah, but it's not important though, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.60,0:27:24.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,-真的不重要吗  -并没有什么意义\N{\fs90}- Is it not? - It's just not relevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.37,0:27:25.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 好吧\N{\fs90}Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.93,0:27:28.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,直线加速赛的意义就是看谁先通过终点\N{\fs90}In a drag race, it's irrelevant which car gets there first?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.67,0:27:31.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 你这辆更适合当送奶车\N{\fs90}Yeah, yours is the better milk float.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.34,0:27:38.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,回到P房 哈蒙德想出了下一个测试\N{\fs90}Back in the pits, Hammond had an idea for the next test.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.78,0:27:41.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们要开车去酒店 离这里大概有一个小时\N{\fs90}We've got to drive to the hotel yet. It's about an hour away.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.67,0:27:44.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,正好给了我们一个机会 看看它们在公路上的表现\N{\fs90}It gives us a chance to see what they're like on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.52,0:27:46.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,-很有道理  -回到现实世界\N{\fs90}- That's a good point. - Real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.92,0:27:49.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,-点子不错  -我做不到\N{\fs90}- That is a good point. - I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.51,0:27:52.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不能把拉法开上路\N{\fs90}I can't drive the Ferrari on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.06,0:27:54.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,-为什么  -这辆车还没注册\N{\fs90}- Why? - It's not registered.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.11,0:27:56.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是啊 上面还挂着牌照呢\N{\fs90}It is, it's got number plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.10,0:27:57.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 那只是个假的牌照\N{\fs90}No, that's just pretend number plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.96,0:27:59.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果注册了的话 这辆车就变成二手车了\N{\fs90}If they register it, it becomes second-hand
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.90,0:28:01.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,还要交税 所以我才用卡车运过来\N{\fs90}and they pay tax. That's why it came in the lorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.74,0:28:03.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以你也不能把它开上路\N{\fs90}So you can't drive it on the road either?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.79,0:28:05.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,谁也不行 上路是非法的\N{\fs90}Nobody can drive it. It's not road legal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.81,0:28:08.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,-噢 不  -兄弟 真扫兴\N{\fs90}- Oh, no. - Mate, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.51,0:28:11.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,-太遗憾了  -你要开一个小时的\N{\fs90}- That is such a shame. - It's an hour of-
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.15,0:28:13.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,你今天真是太不走运了\N{\fs90}That's really a rotten bit of luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.25,0:28:15.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,从意大利千里遥遥地开过来\N{\fs90}'Cause you've come a long way from Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.42,0:28:17.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,我也不能带你一程\N{\fs90}I can't give you a lift
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.25,0:28:20.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为录音师的设备都在副驾座位上\N{\fs90}'cause the soundman's headphones are on the seat and the mixer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.16,0:28:21.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,太惨了\N{\fs90}Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.92,0:28:23.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,我真的无能为力了\N{\fs90}There's literally nothing I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.09,0:28:29.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,不久之后 理查德和我便开始享受\N{\fs90}Soon Richard and I were enjoying
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.85,0:28:32.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,世界上最美妙的一段旅程了\N{\fs90}the world's best-ever commute.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.97,0:28:42.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,内饰看起来可能有些粗犷\N{\fs90}It may be a bit Spartan in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.29,0:28:44.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,但开起来却出人意料地舒适\N{\fs90}but it's unbelievably comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.45,0:28:48.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它的防倾杆\N{\fs90}Because it uses electronics
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.72,0:28:50.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,已经电子化了\N{\fs90}rather than traditional anti-roll bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.00,0:28:53.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,也就是说车轮之间\N{\fs90}That means there's no physical connection
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.25,0:28:55.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有机械上的连接\N{\fs90}between the wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.06,0:28:58.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以当一个车轮遇到颠簸的时候 其他车轮不会受到影响\N{\fs90}So if one goes over a bump the others aren't affected.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.68,0:29:02.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,太不可思议了 就像在开劳斯莱斯幻影\N{\fs90}It's uncanny. It's like being in a Rolls-Royce Phantom.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.73,0:29:09.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,美妙的傍晚 把顶棚拆下来\N{\fs90}It's a lovely evening. Taken the roof panels out.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.50,0:29:11.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,空调开到合适的温度\N{\fs90}Set the air-con just so.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.57,0:29:13.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,享受在这乡间开车的感觉\N{\fs90}And I'm enjoying a drive in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.56,0:29:28.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,与此同时\N{\fs90}Meanwhile...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.72,0:30:06.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,我勒个擦\N{\fs90}Oh, bloody hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.74,0:30:11.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,倒 倒 倒\N{\fs90}You're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.86,0:30:13.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,意大利语的 倒 倒 倒\N{\fs90}You're all right, in Italian.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.47,0:30:24.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,天啊\N{\fs90}Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.61,0:30:33.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,-詹姆斯 -干啥\N{\fs90}- James. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.74,0:30:36.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,抱歉我必须要说 法拉利太没用了\N{\fs90}I'm sorry to have to say this, but that Ferrari is useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.48,0:30:38.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,好好好 一会第二节\N{\fs90}Yes, yes, yes. Later on in part two,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.02,0:30:41.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,这哥俩终于放弃那些\N{\fs90}when these two have stopped dreaming up
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.52,0:30:43.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,我没法参加 又毫不相关的\N{\fs90}idiotic and irrelevant tests
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.19,0:30:47.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,愚蠢测试 我们再见分晓\N{\fs90}that it can't take part in, we shall see.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.06,0:30:48.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,行行行 这个环节里\N{\fs90}Fair enough. Now,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.86,0:30:51.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们仨坐下聊聊\N{\fs90}at this point in the show we like to sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.36,0:30:54.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,新车和汽车行业的那些事\N{\fs90}and chew the fat about new cars and motoring issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.83,0:30:58.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,比如 凭啥英国要在修路期间限速80\N{\fs90}Like, for example, why in Britain we have to drive at 50 miles an hour
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.54,0:31:02.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而并没有人在干活\N{\fs90}when they're doing roadworks to protect the workforce which is never there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.21,0:31:03.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧好吧\N{\fs90}Yes, okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.87,0:31:05.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且为啥那些成熟的成年人\N{\fs90}And why fully-grown adults
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.88,0:31:09.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,要骑着儿童玩具在城市穿梭呢\N{\fs90}have taken to riding around the city on children's toys?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.35,0:31:11.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是 没错-我觉得那叫自行车\N{\fs90}- Yes, okay. - I think they're called bicycles.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.90,0:31:14.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这词没错吧-并不是那样的问题\N{\fs90}- Is that the right word? - It's issues like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.86,0:31:17.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个环节叫做唠嗑街\N{\fs90}It's a segment we are calling Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.16,0:31:28.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,-额-咋了\N{\fs90}- Well... - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.23,0:31:32.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们可是在这视频里下了很多功夫\N{\fs90}We put a lot of work into that!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.57,0:31:36.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个真是非常非常难做\N{\fs90}It was really, really hard doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.51,0:31:39.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,更赞的是 我们很到位地\N{\fs90}Better than that, rather brilliantly, we have made
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.95,0:31:42.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,给接下来每集的这个环节\N{\fs90}a bespoke version of that sting
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.31,0:31:43.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,都定制了个片头\N{\fs90}for every single episode
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.81,0:31:46.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,接下来三年里 每集都不一样\N{\fs90}we're gonna make for the next three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.08,0:31:48.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,怎么样\N{\fs90}How about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.19,0:31:52.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,打断一下 这里有个小问题\N{\fs90}But hold on. The slight problem with that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.46,0:31:54.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们之前一直忙着做这片头\N{\fs90}is that we were so busy doing that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.26,0:31:57.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,以至于没想过这个环节里到底唠什么\N{\fs90}we didn't think actually of anything to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.26,0:31:59.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们想过啊-是啊\N{\fs90}- We did. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.06,0:32:01.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,-啥-你们肯定喜欢\N{\fs90}- What? - You'll love this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.30,0:32:07.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 梅 世界上移动速度最慢的人类\N{\fs90}James May, the world's slowest moving human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.24,0:32:10.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,居然被抓到超速\N{\fs90}has been caught speeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.24,0:32:15.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的被警方罚款\N{\fs90}Actually charged by the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.08,0:32:17.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,罪犯\N{\fs90}Criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.71,0:32:19.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,其实他对这事挺自豪的\N{\fs90}He's actually quite proud of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.25,0:32:22.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,他当时骑着本田CBR 600RR摩托\N{\fs90}He did it on a Honda CBR 600RR sports bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.45,0:32:26.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,事实上...\N{\fs90}The thing was...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.16,0:32:30.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,理查德和我大吃一惊\N{\fs90}Richard and I were genuinely astonished.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.90,0:32:32.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,他跑到办公室来说\N{\fs90}He came into the office and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.83,0:32:34.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,我超速被抓了\N{\fs90}"I've been done for speeding."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.70,0:32:37.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,直到我们发现他到底开多快\N{\fs90}Until we found out how fast he was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.70,0:32:40.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 当时开多快\N{\fs90}James, how fast was it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.14,0:32:43.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,59公里时速\N{\fs90}37 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.08,0:32:45.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,狂人 真是牛逼\N{\fs90}Crazy! Mad man!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.94,0:32:49.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,那么快的速度 你是怎么呼吸的\N{\fs90}How did you even breathe at that kind of speed?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.03,0:32:52.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,警察怎么抓到你的 用腿跑吗\N{\fs90}How did the police catch you? Were they running?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.48,0:32:55.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,肯定是慢跑追上你的\N{\fs90}Gentle jog for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.92,0:32:57.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,要是你也被抓过超速\N{\fs90}The thing is, if you've been caught,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.95,0:33:01.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们真不信这世上还有人会这样\N{\fs90}'cause we genuinely don't believe anyone in the world has,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.58,0:33:05.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你曾被小于59的时速抓超速\N{\fs90}but if you've been caught speeding at a speed less than 37,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.16,0:33:08.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,请写信告诉我们\N{\fs90}do honestly please write to us and let us know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.23,0:33:10.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我们实在是觉得不太可能\N{\fs90}'Cause we don't think it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.23,0:33:12.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,在你的信封写上 我是乌龟\N{\fs90}And mark your envelope, "I'm a tortoise."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.75,0:33:15.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是本期唠嗑街\N{\fs90}And that is all we have time for this week
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.24,0:33:16.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,的全部内容\N{\fs90}on Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.64,0:33:18.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,-等等等等-干啥\N{\fs90}- Whoa! Hang on a minute. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.01,0:33:19.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,这可是第一集 你们俩上来\N{\fs90}The first-ever show, and you just mock me
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.96,0:33:21.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,嘲笑一下我的罚单就结束了\N{\fs90}for my speeding ticket and then we move on?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.88,0:33:23.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,这节目时间很紧的\N{\fs90}It's a busy show.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.85,0:33:26.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,时间那么紧 我们得向观众介绍我们的赛道\N{\fs90}It is a busy show. We've got to tell everyone about our track.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.95,0:33:29.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯 我们真有赛道的\N{\fs90}Yes, we have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.99,0:33:32.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是个你要在街上\N{\fs90}This is the sort of place where you can drive cars
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.96,0:33:34.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,也这么开车的话\N{\fs90}at speeds that you can do on the road
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.89,0:33:37.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,就会被扔进监狱的地方\N{\fs90}but only if you want to go to prison afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.53,0:33:39.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,比如开到60\N{\fs90}What, like 38 miles an hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.30,0:33:42.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,甚至61 62这样\N{\fs90}39 maybe even, 40 from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.00,0:33:45.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,本来呢 我们打算着\N{\fs90}Now, we were hoping that we could bring it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.02,0:33:47.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,把赛道和帐篷一起打包带走\N{\fs90}round the world with us like the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.01,0:33:50.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,但可惜 它太沉了\N{\fs90}But unfortunately it's too heavy,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.77,0:33:53.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且如你即将所见 特别爱咬人\N{\fs90}and, as you are about to see, too bitey.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.41,0:34:00.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这个\N{\fs90}This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.45,0:34:02.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不是赛道\N{\fs90}It's not a race circuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.95,0:34:05.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,也不是机场\N{\fs90}It's not an airfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.42,0:34:07.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,也不是公路\N{\fs90}It's not a road.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.92,0:34:11.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,它是出色和速度的结合体\N{\fs90}What it is is brilliant and fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.50,0:34:14.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且及其危险\N{\fs90}And extremely dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.10,0:34:18.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,地图上看着也危险\N{\fs90}It even looks dangerous on a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.37,0:34:21.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你看 这形状跟埃博拉病毒\N{\fs90}Because as you can see, it's the exact same shape
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.74,0:34:23.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,一模一样\N{\fs90}as the Ebola virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.11,0:34:29.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在就带你们看看这赛道什么样\N{\fs90}Right, time now to show you what a lap looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.93,0:34:33.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了这 我们选了性能标杆\N{\fs90}To do that we've got a bit of a performance benchmark.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.72,0:34:35.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,法拉利488\N{\fs90}A Ferrari 488.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.74,0:34:37.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,走你\N{\fs90}Take it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.72,0:34:41.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,你倒是走啊\N{\fs90}Take it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.13,0:34:47.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,首先是 不直道\N{\fs90}First up, it's the Isn't Straight,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.10,0:34:49.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它真的不直\N{\fs90}so called because it isn't straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.00,0:34:54.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,极速左弯紧随一个极速右弯\N{\fs90}There is a super-fast left followed by a super-fast right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.24,0:34:58.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你犯错 这可没有缓冲区或防护挡板\N{\fs90}And if you make a mistake, there's no run-off area or Armco.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.44,0:35:01.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,直接就进树林了\N{\fs90}It's just woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.71,0:35:03.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,全是野生动物\N{\fs90}Woods that are full of wildlife
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.71,0:35:06.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,喜欢朝你冲过来\N{\fs90}which likes to run out in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.79,0:35:11.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,过了不直道的第二个右弯\N{\fs90}After the second right on the Isn't Straight,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.99,0:35:14.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们就来到了留你名弯\N{\fs90}we're into Your Name Here Corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.26,0:35:19.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,各种赞助冠名机会在此\N{\fs90}Sponsorship opportunities are available here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.03,0:35:21.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我得说明一下\N{\fs90}However, I should explain
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.03,0:35:24.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,可能没人会看你的条幅\N{\fs90}that it's possible nobody will be looking at your banner
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.17,0:35:26.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这个弯被设计成让车来做...\N{\fs90}because this is a corner that was designed
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.54,0:35:28.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,...这事的\N{\fs90}so a car can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.39,0:35:43.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们\N{\fs90}Ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.65,0:35:45.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 梅 今天并没有来\N{\fs90}James May... isn't here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.97,0:35:48.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个只是我一个朋友\N{\fs90}That's just a friend of mine
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.22,0:35:52.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,在他回到不直道之后...\N{\fs90}on his way back up the Isn't Straight...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.43,0:35:54.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,就到了外婆家弯\N{\fs90}towards Old Lady's House.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.33,0:35:59.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们把这叫外婆家\N{\fs90}We've called this section Old Lady's House,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.04,0:36:01.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是因为这旁边有个房子\N{\fs90}because it's right next to a house
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.07,0:36:04.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,住着一个老奶奶\N{\fs90}where an old lady lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.34,0:36:07.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,她跟我们说她喜欢车\N{\fs90}She tells us she likes cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.40,0:36:10.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,她说她之前有一辆车\N{\fs90}Says she used to have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.38,0:36:13.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,不太确定她在我们这么折腾之后\N{\fs90}Not sure she's going to like them quite so much
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.35,0:36:15.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,还会不会喜欢车了\N{\fs90}after we've been here a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.45,0:36:21.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,紧接着就是一个狭窄颠簸的冲刺\N{\fs90}Next up, there's a narrow and bumpy sprint
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.36,0:36:24.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,直到变电箱\N{\fs90}to Sub Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.06,0:36:26.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,你得处理好这个90度左弯\N{\fs90}You need to get this 90-left right,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.43,0:36:29.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,不然你就栽进全是电的笼子里\N{\fs90}or you'll crash into a cage full of electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.60,0:36:34.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,最后一个90度左弯也得如此\N{\fs90}And you'll need to get the final 90-left right as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.94,0:36:37.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,不然就会冲进羊群里\N{\fs90}or you'll run into a field of sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.34,0:36:43.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,那么 树啊 小动物啊\N{\fs90}So, trees, animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.45,0:36:45.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,房子啊 电啊\N{\fs90}a house, electricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.48,0:36:47.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且还是在英国\N{\fs90}and because it's in England,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.32,0:36:49.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,空气一直都很潮\N{\fs90}usually quite a lot of moisture in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.49,0:36:53.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,这真是世界上最危险的赛道\N{\fs90}It really is the most dangerous track anywhere in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.93,0:36:55.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了能在这个赛道留下你的记录\N{\fs90}To post a fast time here,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.96,0:36:59.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,你真的要\N{\fs90}you do need...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.60,0:37:01.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,那些\N{\fs90}those.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.30,0:37:10.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,我选择下埃博拉症赛道的车\N{\fs90}The car I've selected for my first lap
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.31,0:37:12.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这个\N{\fs90}of the Eboladrome is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.51,0:37:18.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,宝马M2\N{\fs90}The BMW M2.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.33,0:37:36.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,遗憾的是 在我们第一集节目里\N{\fs90}Sadly, there isn't the time in this, our first-ever show,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.57,0:37:40.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,没时间做公路测评了\N{\fs90}to do a full road test of this car,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.04,0:37:43.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过我倒是有时间说\N{\fs90}but there is time to say that I think
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.73,0:37:47.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得这是宝马有史以来最棒的M\N{\fs90}this is the best M car BMW has ever made.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.89,0:38:02.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,这年头很多性能车\N{\fs90}In a lot of fast cars these days,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.93,0:38:05.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,都装了各种旋钮 按钮\N{\fs90}you get all sorts of knobs and buttons
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.13,0:38:07.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,用来改变-\N{\fs90}which you can use to change-
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.20,0:38:09.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说改变 其实是毁了\N{\fs90}I say change- I mean ruin
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.20,0:38:10.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,引擎 悬挂\N{\fs90}the characteristics of the engine
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.63,0:38:13.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,和转向等的个性\N{\fs90}and the suspension and the steering and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.20,0:38:15.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一直觉得 这就像个厨子\N{\fs90}And I always think, isn't that like a chef
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.74,0:38:17.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,把鱼给你端上桌\N{\fs90}bringing a fish to your table
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.54,0:38:20.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后放上烤炉 黄油 一点西芹\N{\fs90}and an oven and some butter and a bit of parsley,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.18,0:38:22.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后说 你自己做吧 才不要啊\N{\fs90}and saying, "Cook it yourself"? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.38,0:38:24.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,你来烧啊 我花钱就为了这个\N{\fs90}You cook it, it's what I'm paying for.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.92,0:38:27.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,可喜的是 这辆车\N{\fs90}This car, happily, has a more
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.95,0:38:29.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,更回归本质一些\N{\fs90}back-to-basics approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.75,0:38:32.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,M2里面 下面有个小开关\N{\fs90}In the M2 you get a little rocker switch down here
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.62,0:38:35.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,完全没有用\N{\fs90}which does nothing at all
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.29,0:38:38.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,就我来看 就这么多\N{\fs90}as far as I can see, and that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.39,0:38:41.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,你所买到的车在出厂前\N{\fs90}You're buying a car which was set up at the factory
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.37,0:38:45.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,就由那些知道自己该干嘛的工程师设置好了一切\N{\fs90}by engineers who know what they're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.07,0:38:47.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,而你要做的就是好好享受驾驶乐趣\N{\fs90}And all you have to do is enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.77,0:38:51.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像我现在这样\N{\fs90}Which I am doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.55,0:38:59.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,爽啊 看看这个\N{\fs90}Yes, look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.53,0:39:01.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,太喜欢这个了\N{\fs90}Oh, yeah, loving that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.29,0:39:06.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要再做一次 来验证-\N{\fs90}I'll do that again, actually, and make sure-
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.19,0:39:08.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,来验证我是对的\N{\fs90}make sure I was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.97,0:39:18.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,几乎就没有什么转向不足\N{\fs90}There's hardly any understeer at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.37,0:39:20.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,尾巴甩出去 保持住\N{\fs90}Poke the back out and hold it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.74,0:39:23.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶\N{\fs90}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.54,0:39:25.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,再来一次\N{\fs90}I'll do that again...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.39,0:39:27.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,反过来\N{\fs90}only going the other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.18,0:39:29.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,开留你名弯\N{\fs90}Wrong way round Your Name Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.12,0:39:36.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,克劳斯和弗瑞茨 我爱你们的作品\N{\fs90}Klaus and Fritz, I am loving your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.72,0:39:40.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,哎呀 我搞砸了 但我只要这样\N{\fs90}Oh, I made a mess of that. But I'll just do this,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.53,0:39:43.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,就能让一切看起来像是故意的\N{\fs90}and it'll look like I did it on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.63,0:39:47.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,随着轮胎不停求饶\N{\fs90}With the tires begging for mercy,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.10,0:39:48.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我来到了不直道\N{\fs90}I got back onto the Isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.76,0:39:52.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后把这3.0升直6双涡轮发动机的\N{\fs90}and unleashed 365 rampaging horsepowers
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.64,0:39:56.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,365马力狂暴的释放了出来\N{\fs90}from the turbo-charged three-liter straight six.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.04,0:40:01.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,跟M3比 这车直路并不快\N{\fs90}This isn't as fast in a straight line
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.05,0:40:03.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过除此之外一切...\N{\fs90}as an M3, but everywhere else...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.81,0:40:05.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,都更棒\N{\fs90}it is better.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.62,0:40:09.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,感觉更轻 更灵活\N{\fs90}It feels less heavy, less cumbersome.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.62,0:40:18.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且我们这个直道的特性\N{\fs90}And due to the unique characteristics of our straight,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.20,0:40:21.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能感觉到转向没那么\N{\fs90}I can tell the steering is less...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.13,0:40:23.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,焦躁\N{\fs90}It's less twitchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.14,0:40:31.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个赛道就是为了刁难车的\N{\fs90}This track was designed to trip cars up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.88,0:40:34.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里有极速弯\N{\fs90}There are fast corners,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.05,0:40:35.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,慢速弯\N{\fs90}slow corners,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.88,0:40:38.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,漂移弯 还有颠簸\N{\fs90}drifty corners, and bumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.33,0:40:40.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,对轮胎\N{\fs90}It's hard on the tires.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.72,0:40:44.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,刹车 引擎都有着极大的考验\N{\fs90}It's hard on the brakes. It's hard on the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.36,0:40:48.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,危机四伏 让你尖叫\N{\fs90}It's point and squirt and bark and yelp.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.13,0:40:50.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,极其凶狠\N{\fs90}It is vicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.61,0:40:57.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这些都无法难倒M2\N{\fs90}But there is nothing here which has flummoxed the M2.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.39,0:41:01.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,这绝对是惊世之作\N{\fs90}This thing is an absolute masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.89,0:41:07.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,像我说的 这是宝马造过\N{\fs90}Like I said, it is the best M car
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.06,0:41:09.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,最棒的一辆M了\N{\fs90}BMW has ever made.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.73,0:41:14.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,你可能会觉得我疯了\N{\fs90}You may think it's mad to suggest
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.25,0:41:16.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,认为最便宜的M是最好的\N{\fs90}the cheapest M car is the best,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.74,0:41:18.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,但要这样看\N{\fs90}but look at it this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.54,0:41:21.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个赛道比银石赛道便宜很多\N{\fs90}this track is a lot cheaper than Silverstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.64,0:41:24.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,我却知道我已心有所属\N{\fs90}And I know which one I'd rather drive round.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.92,0:41:38.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,去开开M2吧 令人难以置信\N{\fs90}Go drive an M2. Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.99,0:41:42.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\fs90}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.06,0:41:45.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,老奶奶家那里怎么有连续弯\N{\fs90}Why is there that zigzag at Old Lady's House?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.60,0:41:47.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,我去时不是这样啊 -对 那时是的\N{\fs90}- That wasn't there when I went. - No, that wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.80,0:41:50.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是你走了之后 我们发现\N{\fs90}But after you'd left, we discovered there is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.24,0:41:52.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,那有一颗没爆的二战炸弹 讲真\N{\fs90}an unexploded Second World War bomb, seriously,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.61,0:41:56.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,就在赛道的位置 所以要绕开它\N{\fs90}right where the track was, so we had to go round it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.44,0:41:59.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,有道理 -我总结下\N{\fs90}- Fair enough. - Let me get this right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.11,0:42:01.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我们的赛道上 有树 动物\N{\fs90}At our track, there's trees, animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.75,0:42:03.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,湿气 电气设备\N{\fs90}moisture, electricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.55,0:42:05.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,一栋房子 和一个没爆的炸弹\N{\fs90}a house, and an unexploded bomb?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.59,0:42:08.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 像我说的 这是世界上最危险的赛道\N{\fs90}Yeah. Like I said, it's the most dangerous track in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.56,0:42:12.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,讲真 它让伊莫拉变得像过家家一样\N{\fs90}Honestly, it makes Imola look like a duvet. Honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.46,0:42:16.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管怎样 我们在埃博拉症赛道测的每一辆车\N{\fs90}Anyway, all the cars that we test at the Eboladrome
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.33,0:42:18.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,都会跑一个计时圈\N{\fs90}will do a timed lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.13,0:42:20.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了确保条件公平\N{\fs90}And to make sure it's a completely level playing field,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.74,0:42:24.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们都会由同一位车手驾驶\N{\fs90}they will all be driven by the same racing driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.71,0:42:26.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦\N{\fs90}Ooh!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.51,0:42:28.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们想到这点了 我们动过脑子了\N{\fs90}We thought about this. We gave it some thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.78,0:42:30.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们多机智  现在\N{\fs90}How clever is that? Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.11,0:42:34.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,问题是 亚马逊坚持\N{\fs90}The thing is, Amazon insisted
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.48,0:42:36.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们要选的车手\N{\fs90}that the racing driver in question
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.35,0:42:39.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,必须是大洋这边的人\N{\fs90}should be from this side of the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.32,0:42:42.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们去了一个叫纳斯卡的地方\N{\fs90}So we went to something called NASCAR?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.22,0:42:44.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,找了一个 把他运到英国\N{\fs90}And we found one. We shipped him to England
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.86,0:42:48.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后教给他一套复杂的动作\N{\fs90}and then we introduced him to the complicated procedure
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.16,0:42:50.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,其中包括 向右转弯\N{\fs90}which involves turning right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.82,0:42:53.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,他叫麦克 斯吉那\N{\fs90}He's called Mike Skinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.40,0:42:56.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我们只管他叫 老美\N{\fs90}but we know him simply as "the American."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.04,0:42:57.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,需要提醒你的是\N{\fs90}We should warn you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.70,0:43:00.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,他有些观点十分强硬\N{\fs90}that some of his views are quite strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.67,0:43:03.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 他的观点非常明确 比如\N{\fs90}Yes, he has very specific views, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.38,0:43:05.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,气缸数少于8个的车\N{\fs90}on cars that have engines with fewer than eight cylinders.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.81,0:43:07.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我党 -或多于8缸的车\N{\fs90}- Communist. - Or more than eight cylinders.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.98,0:43:11.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我党 -发动机在中间的车\N{\fs90}- Communist. - Or cars that have their engine in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.25,0:43:13.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,我党\N{\fs90}Communist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.22,0:43:16.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,一切非美式V8的都是我党\N{\fs90}Everything that isn't American really with a V8 is communist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.36,0:43:19.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以让我们看看他和M2相处如何\N{\fs90}So let's see how he gets on with the M2.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.43,0:43:21.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,他就在这了\N{\fs90}There he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.43,0:43:23.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,不知所措 东张西望\N{\fs90}Looking utterly bewildered.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.50,0:43:28.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是他出发了 稍稍打滑\N{\fs90}But he's off. A skitter of a wheel spin.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.80,0:43:31.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,立马进入不直道\N{\fs90}And immediately he's onto the Isn't Straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.24,0:43:33.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,这有个让他困扰的右弯\N{\fs90}There is a right there that will have confused him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.74,0:43:35.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,接着左弯 他应该很擅长\N{\fs90}Now a left, he'll be good at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.28,0:43:38.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,可以油门全开了\N{\fs90}Now he can open the taps.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.05,0:43:40.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,3.0升 6缸\N{\fs90}Three liters, six cylinders.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.75,0:43:42.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,这东西连狗屁股里的油绳\N{\fs90}This thing wouldn't pull a greasy string
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.48,0:43:44.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,都拔不出来\N{\fs90}out of a dog's ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.35,0:43:49.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,我完全不明白他在说什么\N{\fs90}I've literally no idea what he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.26,0:43:51.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我的家乡 这不是一辆车\N{\fs90}Where I come from, this ain't a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.99,0:43:54.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是求助的哭喊\N{\fs90}It's a cry for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.23,0:43:56.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,管他吧\N{\fs90}Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.03,0:43:58.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,开过了不直道的最后一个弯\N{\fs90}He's through the final corner on the Isn't Straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.43,0:44:01.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,进入留你名弯 大力刹车\N{\fs90}Into Your Name Here. Hard on the brakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.24,0:44:03.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,紧握换挡杆\N{\fs90}Grabbing the stick,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.20,0:44:05.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然挡杆现在在他左边了\N{\fs90}which is on the left-hand side of where he's sitting,
